--[[
  USEFUL FUNCTIONS
--]]

function GetSnapPointWorldPosition(obj, snapPointNum)
  snapPosition = obj.getSnapPoints()[snapPointNum].position
  snapPosition.x = obj.getScale().x * snapPosition.x + obj.getPosition().x
  snapPosition.y = obj.getScale().y * snapPosition.y + 1 + obj.getPosition().y
  snapPosition.z = obj.getScale().z * snapPosition.z + obj.getPosition().z
  return snapPosition
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
playerCount = 5

function RollDice() -- roll the auction dice
  ClearAuction()
  -- init
  dice = {}
  dice[1] = getObjectFromGUID("ad5c10")
  dice[2] = getObjectFromGUID("a33d3a")
  dice[3] = getObjectFromGUID("857031")
  dice[4] = getObjectFromGUID("37be45")
  dice[5] = getObjectFromGUID("671cb6")
  diceTray = getObjectFromGUID("f215f3")
  -- check the amount of players, and roll the corresponding die
  for i = playerCount,1,-1  do
    dice[i].setPosition({diceTray.getPosition().x + 3 - i,diceTray.getPosition().y + 1,diceTray.getPosition().z})
    dice[i].Roll()
    dice[i].Roll()
  end

  -- setup wait function until the dice stop rolling
  Wait.condition(
    function() -- set up the auction plate
      SetAuction(dice)
    end,
    function() -- Check if the dice are level
      return CheckDice()
    end
  )
end

function CheckDice() -- check the dice state
  for i, die in ipairs(dice) do
    if (die != null) then
      if not (die.resting) then return false end
      end
    end
  return true
end

function SetAuction(dice) -- for each die, update the auction
  for i = playerCount,1,-1  do
    moveMaoiToAuction(dice[i],i)
  end
  firstTurnFlag = false -- remove first round flag
  --EndRound1()
end

function moveMaoiToAuction(inDice,i) -- move maoi from bag to auction
  -- init
  auctionPlate = getObjectFromGUID("f3d588")
  smallBag = getObjectFromGUID("ce3dae")
  medBag = getObjectFromGUID("02ac30")
  largeBag = getObjectFromGUID("a225db")
  placePosition = GetSnapPointWorldPosition(auctionPlate,i)
  --placePosition = Global.call('GetSnapPointWorldPosition',{auctionPlate, i})
  firstTurnFlag = getObjectFromGUID("de1bed").getValue() == 1
  if (inDice.getRotationValue() == 1 and firstTurnFlag) then
    smallBag.takeObject(
    {
      position          = placePosition,
      smooth            = true
    })
  end
  if (inDice.getRotationValue() == 2 or inDice.getRotationValue() == 3) then
    smallBag.takeObject(
    {
      position          = placePosition,
      smooth            = true
    })
  end
  if (inDice.getRotationValue() == 4 or inDice.getRotationValue() == 5) then
    medBag.takeObject(
    {
      position          = placePosition,
      smooth            = true
    })
  end
  if (inDice.getRotationValue() == 6 and firstTurnFlag) then
    medBag.takeObject(
    {
      position          = placePosition,
      smooth            = true
    })
  elseif (inDice.getRotationValue() == 6) then
    largeBag.takeObject(
    {
      position          = placePosition,
      smooth            = true
    })
  end
end

function ClearAuction()
  --init
  auctionScriptZ = getObjectFromGUID('d7fe55')
  smallBag = getObjectFromGUID("ce3dae")
  medBag = getObjectFromGUID("02ac30")
  largeBag = getObjectFromGUID("a225db")
  --move any remaining Maoi back to their corresponding bag
  for i, maoi in ipairs(auctionScriptZ.getObjects()) do
    if (maoi.hasTag('small')) then
      smallBag.putObject(maoi)
    elseif(maoi.hasTag('medium')) then
      medBag.putObject(maoi)
    elseif(maoi.hasTag('large')) then
      largeBag.putObject(maoi)
    end
  end
end

function GetSnapPointWorldPosition(obj, snapPointNum)
  snapPosition = obj.getSnapPoints()[snapPointNum].position
  snapPosition.x = obj.getScale().x * snapPosition.x + obj.getPosition().x
  snapPosition.y = obj.getScale().y * snapPosition.y + 1 + obj.getPosition().y
  snapPosition.z = obj.getScale().z * snapPosition.z + obj.getPosition().z
  return snapPosition
end
